  <prompt>
    Execute the project wrap-up per `task-create` Step 3.7 protocol. This is the final task of R3 — it verifies every wave's deliverable holds, fixes any cross-cutting issues found by `/code-review` + `/adr-check`, archives ephemera, updates project-level status docs, and codifies lessons-learned for future R-class projects.

    The wrap-up is a checkpoint, not a rubber stamp. If `/code-review` finds Critical issues across waves OR `/adr-check` finds violations, this task fixes them BEFORE marking project complete.
