  <notes>
    This is the FULL-rigor task per CLAUDE.md §8 decision tree. Quality gates (code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5) ARE run within this task's own steps (1–4) — they are the task's primary purpose.

    Empirical findings from project pipeline (essential for lessons-learned):
    - LegalWorkspace fork count delta (CLAUDE.md finding #9): only `CreateMatter/SendEmailStep.tsx` was a true fork. Project/Event/Todo/WorkAssignment dirs existed but no email step. Wave 5 scope was smaller than spec implied.
    - `sprk_communication_send.js` LOC delta (CLAUDE.md finding #7): ~1,150 LOC per copy × 2 copies (~2,300 LOC total) vs spec's stated ~600 LOC.
    - UQ3 resolution: Wave 0 task 003 chose the Internet-Message-Id retrieval strategy via 1-hour spike. Record final strategy choice in lessons-learned.
    - PR #360 collision handling: tasks 086, 087, 088, 091 had to coordinate rebase with active PR #360 (audit-r1-docs-update) touching `.claude/patterns/`, `.claude/constraints/`, `docs/architecture/`. Capture coordination approach.
    - UQ1 resolution: Wave 2 task 035 audited standard form customizations; document the migration path chosen.
    - Owner clarification "single PR for 5 wizards" (Wave 5): capture how that shipped + the review-burden trade-off.

    Post-completion handoff: after this task is ✅, the project is ready for `/merge-to-master`. Do NOT run merge-to-master from inside this task — it's the next discrete action.
  </notes>

